ivardefs.name: contact_
ivardefs.desc: Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher.

ivardefs.name: date
ivardefs.desc: The date  (and optionally time) when the graph definition was published. The date must change when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the graph definiti

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: A free text natural language description of the graph definition from a consumer's perspective.

ivardefs.name: experimental
ivardefs.desc: A Boolean value to indicate that this graph definition is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing) and is not intended to be used for genuine usage.

ivardefs.name: jurisdiction_
ivardefs.desc: A legal or geographic region in which the graph definition is intended to be used.

ivardefs.name: link_
ivardefs.desc: Links this graph makes rules about.

ivardefs.name: name
ivardefs.desc: A natural language name identifying the graph definition. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation.

ivardefs.name: profile
ivardefs.desc: The profile that describes the use of the base resource.

ivardefs.name: publisher
ivardefs.desc: The name of the organization or individual that published the graph definition.

ivardefs.name: purpose
ivardefs.desc: Explanation of why this graph definition is needed and why it has been designed as it has.

ivardefs.name: start
ivardefs.desc: The type of FHIR resource at which instances of this graph start.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of this graph definition. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content.

ivardefs.name: url
ivardefs.desc: An absolute URI that is used to identify this graph definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance; also called its canonical identifier. This SHOULD be globally unique and SHOULD be a literal address at which at which a

ivardefs.name: useContext_
ivardefs.desc: The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These contexts may be general categories (gender, age, ...) or may be references to specific programs (insurance plans, studies, ...) and may be used to assist w

ivardefs.name: version
ivardefs.desc: The identifier that is used to identify this version of the graph definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the graph definition author and is not expected to be globally unique.

properties.desc: A formal computable definition of a graph of resources - that is, a coherent set of resources that form a graph by following references. The Graph Definition resource defines a set and makes rules about the set.
